description: Detected uClibc library version 0.9.30.3, no known CVE vulnerabilities found. This library is a commonly used C standard library implementation in embedded systems.

Detected OpenSSL library version 1.0.0, which contains multiple known critical vulnerabilities, including the CCS Injection vulnerability (CVE-2014-0224). This version is outdated and no longer maintained. Immediate upgrade is strongly recommended.

Identified libstdc++ library version 6.0.13, which is an implementation of the GNU C++ standard library. Further verification of the specific GCC version is required to determine relevant vulnerabilities.
Detected multiple BusyBox binary calls, but unable to determine the specific version. BusyBox typically includes multiple utilities, requiring further analysis of its included components.
